<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Peiping (
                        Clubb
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d90</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">90</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-01-23T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-23">January 23,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received January 22—11:57 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>103. ReEmbtel 24, January 23.<note n="41" xml:id="d90fn41">Not found in
                        Department of State files.</note> Political turnover completed presumably
                    effective 10 a. m. January 22 (see Contel 87, January 22<note n="42" xml:id="d90fn42">Telegram No. 97 to the Department, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>).</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ping Ming Jih Pao</hi> reports today Nationalist forces
                    occupying Peiping yesterday were removing from city in direction Huangtsun to
                    south and Huangszu (Yellow Temple) to north, that movement continues today, that
                    it is understood all will have been removed tomorrow, January 24, for stationing
                    outside city.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 93, repeated Department 103, Shanghai 92.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
